        <h3>2.Symptom Relief </h3>
        <p>Medications provide relief from symptoms such as pain, inflammation, high blood pressure, or high blood sugar levels, improving the patient's comfort and well-being.</p>
        <h4>3. Preventing Complications</h4>
        <p>Chronic diseases often lead to complications. Medications can reduce the risk of complications such as heart attacks, strokes, kidney failure, and vision problems in conditions like diabetes and hypertension</p>
        <h5>4.Stabilizing Health</h5>
        <p>Medications help in stabilizing health parameters like blood pressure, blood sugar, cholesterol levels, and inflammation markers, reducing the risk of sudden and severe health episodes.</p>
